<div class="row" style="justify-content: space-between; align-items: flex-start;">
  <div>
    <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">Client: <%= client.name %></h2>
    <div class="muted">ID: <code><%= client.id %></code></div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <a class="btn" href="/clients/<%= client.id %>/slack-install">Add Slack (you)</a>
    <a class="btn" href="/clients/<%= client.id %>/edit">Edit</a>
    <a class="btn" href="/">Back</a>
  </div>
</div>

<% if (publicBase) { %>
  <p class="muted" style="margin:0 0 8px 0;">In your Slack app → <strong>OAuth &amp; Permissions</strong> → <strong>Redirect URLs</strong>, add: <code><%= publicBase %>/auth/slack/callback</code> and save. <strong>Do not</strong> use Slack’s <strong>Install App</strong> in the API site (empty <code>redirect_uri</code>).</p>
  <% if (typeof shareInstallUrl !== 'undefined' && shareInstallUrl) { %>
  <div class="card" style="margin:0 0 14px 0;padding:14px;border:1px solid rgba(110,168,254,0.25);">
    <h4 style="margin:0 0 8px 0;">Link for the customer to install the app in their workspace</h4>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:0 0 8px 0;">Opening this link starts OAuth for <strong>this</strong> client only (the long secret in the path is tied to this client). Send it to someone who can click <strong>Allow</strong> in their Slack. Not for posting publicly.</p>
    <p style="margin:0;word-break:break-all;"><a href="<%= shareInstallUrl %>"><%= shareInstallUrl %></a></p>
    <p style="margin:8px 0 0 0;"><button class="btn" type="button" id="cpyInstall">Copy link</button></p>
    <script>document.getElementById("cpyInstall").addEventListener("click",()=>{navigator.clipboard.writeText(<%= JSON.stringify(shareInstallUrl) %>).catch(()=>{});});</script>
  </div>
  <% } %>
<% } %>

<div class="card">
  <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">Config</h3>
  <div class="grid">
    <div><div class="muted">Slack Channel ID</div><div><code><%= client.slack_channel_id || '' %></code></div></div>
    <div><div class="muted">Status</div><div><span class="pill <%= client.status === 'active' ? 'ok' : 'off' %>"><%= client.status %></span></div></div>
    <div><div class="muted">Slack token (worker)</div><div><%= maskSecret(client.slack_token) %></div></div>
    <div><div class="muted">Prospeo API key</div><div><%= maskSecret(client.prospeo_api_key) %></div></div>
    <div><div class="muted">SmartLead API key</div><div><%= maskSecret(client.smartlead_api_key) %></div></div>
    <div><div class="muted">SmartLead campaign ID</div><div><code><%= client.smartlead_campaign_id || '—' %></code></div></div>
    <div><div class="muted">HeyReach API key</div><div><%= maskSecret(client.heyreach_api_key) %></div></div>
    <div><div class="muted">HeyReach campaign ID</div><div><code><%= client.heyreach_campaign_id || '—' %></code></div></div>
    <div><div class="muted">Slack bot token (UI posts)</div><div><%= maskSecret(client.slack_bot_token_ui) %></div></div>
    <div class="span-2"><div class="muted">Webhook secret (SmartLead / HeyReach URLs)</div><div><code><%= client.webhook_secret || '' %></code></div></div>
  </div>

  <% const hookBase = (typeof publicBase !== 'undefined' && publicBase) ? publicBase : ''; %>
  <% if (hookBase) { %>
  <div style="margin-top: 14px; padding-top: 14px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);">
    <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">Webhooks (first engagement → Slack timing)</h3>
    <p class="muted">Point SmartLead and HeyReach at these URLs. The UI records the lead when the worker enrolls them, then posts visit → first engagement to this client’s Slack channel when the webhook fires.</p>
    <div class="muted" style="margin-bottom: 8px;"><strong>SmartLead</strong> (enable <code>EMAIL_SENT</code> or engagement events you care about)</div>
    <pre style="white-space: pre-wrap;"><%= hookBase %>/hooks/smartlead/<%= client.id %>/<%= client.webhook_secret %></pre>
    <div class="muted" style="margin: 12px 0 8px 0;"><strong>HeyReach</strong> (message / connection events — payload must include LinkedIn URL)</div>
    <pre style="white-space: pre-wrap;"><%= hookBase %>/hooks/heyreach/<%= client.id %>/<%= client.webhook_secret %></pre>
  </div>
  <% } else { %>
  <p class="muted" style="margin-top: 12px;">Set <code>UI_PUBLIC_URL</code> on the UI service (e.g. your Railway domain) to show full webhook URLs here.</p>
  <% } %>

  <% if (client.notes) { %>
    <div style="margin-top: 12px;">
      <div class="muted">Notes</div>
      <pre style="white-space: pre-wrap; background: #0b1020; padding: 10px; border-radius: 10px; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);"><%= client.notes %></pre>
    </div>
  <% } %>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <div class="row" style="justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;">
    <h3 style="margin: 0;">Railway env (worker-v2)</h3>
    <button class="btn" type="button" onclick="copyEnv()">Copy</button>
  </div>
  <p class="muted" style="margin-top: 8px;">Deploy from <code>worker-v2/</code>. Set these variables on the worker; also set <code>WORKER_CONFIG_SECRET</code> on the <strong>UI</strong> service to the same value so the worker can call the config API.</p>
  <textarea id="envBlock" spellcheck="false" style="width: 100%; min-height: 180px; background: #0b1020; color: #e7ecff; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); border-radius: 12px; padding: 12px; font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, 'Liberation Mono', 'Courier New', monospace;"><%= envBlock %></textarea>
</div>

<dialog id="onboardModal" style="max-width: 880px; width: 92vw; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.10); border-radius: 14px; background: #0b1020; color: #e7ecff; padding: 0;">
  <div style="padding: 18px 18px 0 18px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);">
    <div class="row" style="justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;">
      <h3 style="margin: 0;">Client onboarding guide</h3>
      <button class="btn" onclick="document.getElementById('onboardModal').close()">Close</button>
    </div>
    <p class="muted"><strong>Prospeo</strong> can enrich a missing work email. Worker-v2 sends to <strong>SmartLead</strong> when email is available and <strong>HeyReach</strong> when LinkedIn is available.</p>
  </div>
  <div style="padding: 18px;">
    <h4 style="margin-top: 0;">1) RB2B → Slack</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>In RB2B, enable Slack notifications for identified visitors/leads.</li>
      <li>Point RB2B to the client’s Slack workspace/channel for alerts.</li>
      <li>In Slack, copy the channel ID (looks like <code>C0123ABCDEF</code>) and paste it into this client record.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>2) Secrets in this UI</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Slack token (worker)</strong>: bot token with access to read the RB2B alert channel (<code>conversations.history</code>).</li>
      <li><strong>Slack bot token (UI)</strong>: token used by this app to <code>chat.postMessage</code> visit → engagement timing into the same channel.</li>
      <li><strong>Prospeo</strong>, <strong>SmartLead</strong>, and <strong>HeyReach</strong> keys and campaign IDs are stored here and fetched by the worker at runtime.</li>
      <li>Set the same <code>WORKER_CONFIG_SECRET</code> on the UI service and the worker; the worker uses it to call <code>GET /api/worker-config/:clientId</code> and receives the touchpoint ingest secret for enrollments.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>3) Prospeo (email when RB2B has none)</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Worker calls <code>POST https://api.prospeo.io/enrich-person</code> with <code>only_verified_email: true</code> (LinkedIn URL if present, else name + company website/name).</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>4) Deploy worker-v2 on Railway</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Create a service from the <code>worker-v2/</code> folder.</li>
      <li>Set <code>WORKER_CLIENT_ID</code> to this client’s UUID, <code>UI_PUBLIC_URL</code> to the UI URL, and <code>WORKER_CONFIG_SECRET</code> to match the UI service.</li>
      <li>Set the cron schedule (for example every 15 minutes) and command <code>node index.js</code>.</li>
      <li>Leave the legacy worker alone (it stays running for your current client).</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>5) Visit → first engagement (webhooks)</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Set <code>UI_PUBLIC_URL</code> on the UI service so this page shows full webhook URLs.</li>
      <li>In <strong>SmartLead</strong>, point a webhook at the SmartLead URL on this page.</li>
      <li>In <strong>HeyReach</strong>, point a webhook at the HeyReach URL (payload should include a LinkedIn profile URL).</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</dialog>

<div class="row" style="justify-content: flex-end;">
  <button class="btn primary" type="button" onclick="document.getElementById('onboardModal').showModal()">Open onboarding modal</button>
</div>

<script>
  async function copyEnv() {
    const el = document.getElementById('envBlock');
    el.select();
    el.setSelectionRange(0, el.value.length);
    try {
      await navigator.clipboard.writeText(el.value);
    } catch (e) {
      document.execCommand('copy');
    }
  }
</script>
